column1: CAUSE OF DEATH  IN BRISTOL (UNION AND CITY AND COUNTY) (1901 â€“ 1939)
The tuberculosis category included deaths from late effects of tuberculosis.
From 1937 poliomyelitis also included deaths from polioencephalitis.
Cerebro-vascular disease was also known as variously through this period: cerebral haemorrhage, intra-cranial vascular lesions and vascular lesions of the nervous system.
Congenital debility also included malformations and premature birth.
